place.name: STOKE CHARITY
place.gazetteerText: STOKE-CHARITY, a parish in Winchester district, Hants; near Micheldever r. station, and 6½ miles N of Winchester. Post town, Micheldever Station. Acres, 1,850. Real property, £1,595. Pop., 130. Houses, 28. The manor belongs to Sir W. Heathcote. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £389.* Patron, Corpus Christi College, Oxford. The church ranges from Norman to later English. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
